                <note rend="inline" type="source">860j.01/196a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the High Commissioner at Constantinople</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bristol</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-01-27T19:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 27, 1920—7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>29. As United States has not as yet adhered to decision of Supreme Council
                    recognizing the independence of the Armenian Republic, or that of Georgia and
                    Azerbaijan you are authorized to deny any report that this government has
                    accorded such recognitions. Repeat to Haskell<note n="22" xml:id="d936fn22">Col.
                        W. N. Haskell, Allied High Commissioner in Armenia.</note> for similar
                    action.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
